        "body": "Summary\n\nFixes Discord guild-admin message action authorization so privileged Discord admin actions require a trusted Discord requester identity even when the action is invoked from another channel provider.\n\nChanges\n\n- Centralize the Discord privileged guild-admin action list in a shared helper.\n- Require trusted requester identity for those Discord actions regardless of current provider.\n- Reject non-Discord origins in the Discord guild-admin handler instead of dropping the requester identity and continuing through a no-sender path.\n- Keep read-only Discord guild lookups available from non-Discord requesters.\n\nValidation\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-discord.config.ts discord/src/channel-actions.test.ts discord/src/actions/handle-action.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-discord.config.ts discord/src --reporter=dot`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\nReal behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Cross-provider attempts to run privileged Discord guild-admin message actions are rejected unless they originate with a trusted Discord sender identity.\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on branch `747`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-discord.config.ts discord/src --reporter=dot`.\nEvidence after fix: Discord extension lane passed with 158 test files and 1763 tests.\nObserved result after fix: The regression tests now require trusted requester identity across origins and reject non-Discord requester IDs for privileged Discord guild-admin actions while preserving read-only guild lookups.\nWhat was not tested: No live Discord API calls were run; validation used the existing Discord extension unit/runtime boundaries.\n\nNotes\n\n- `CHANGELOG.md` was not updated.\n- `USER.md` was updated locally with the requested worklog and intentionally left out of the commit.\n",
